element.name: Leixlip Gate by Lotsafish & IrishAbi, Traditional Cache (1/1)

description.b:
This is the second in a series of four caches looking at the
historical sites surrounding Castletown Estate.

p.i:
All Caches contain FTF Certificates as the FTF
reward.

long-description.center:
Leixlip Gate
The Leixlip Gate and Gate House are remainders of a long side road leading up to Castletown House. It is not a well known or much reported-on historical part of the Castletown Estate.
The cache is a small size magnetic loc-box wrapped in a black
covering.

We had to kill some time, before heading to the airport; so we decided to look for some cache on the way.
Thanks for this one... Greetings from Portugal
